          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1617029377436-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1617029377436-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1617029377436-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Deseed the<strong> sweet pointed pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</strong> </span>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and finely dice</p><p>Dissolve the<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>ground turmeric </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>tomato paste </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) in 225ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617029392610-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617029392610-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617029392610-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617029392610-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1617029392610-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>diced</strong> <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until they've softened slightly</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1617029433803-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1617029433803-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1617029433803-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1617029433803-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1617029433803-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> white long grain rice</strong>, <strong>tomato stock </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the<strong> chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked – this is your <strong>spicy rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1617029452694-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1617029452694-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1617029452694-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1617029452694-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1617029452694-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>chipotle paste</strong>, <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and <strong>remaining tomato paste</strong> with the juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1] </span><strong>lemon</strong> in a large mixing bowl</p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong>, then give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>peri peri sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1617029461680-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1617029461680-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1617029461680-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1617029461680-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1617029461680-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> flat white mushrooms </strong>to the<strong> peri peri sauce</strong> and give it a good mix up until they are fully coated</p><p>Transfer the <strong>coated mushrooms<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>to a baking tray, stems facing up (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!) and drizzle over any <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>peri peri sauce</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until cooked through and tender – these are your<strong> peri peri mushrooms</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1617029469842-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1617029469842-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1617029469842-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1617029469842-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1617029469842-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lemon </strong>into wedges</p><p>Wash, then shred the<strong> lettuce </strong>and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Combine the <strong>mayo</strong> with the juice of 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]<strong> </span>lemon wedges </strong>and a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>in a large bowl<strong> </strong>–<strong> </strong>this is your<strong> lemon mayo</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> shredded lettuce </strong>to the bowl with the <strong>lemon mayo</strong>, then give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>lemony salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1617029492461-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1617029492461-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
